    <h3><br>
    </h3>
    <h3><br>
    </h3>
    <div class="git General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: DIARRHEA</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site of
          Discomfort</span> <span class="verbal">"Do you have any abdominal
          pain or cramping with the diarrhea? If so, where is it located?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Generalized cramping -&gt; <span class="infectious">Gastroenteritis</span></li>
          <li class="git">Lower Left Quadrant pain -&gt; <span class="git">Diverticulitis</span></li>
          <li class="git">Lower Right Quadrant pain -&gt; <span class="infectious">Infectious
              enterocolitis (Yersinia, Campylobacter), <b class="rheumatic">Crohn's
                Disease</b></span></li>
          <li class="git">Periumbilical pain -&gt; <span class="infectious">Small
              bowel cause, gastroenteritis</span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"When did the diarrhea start? Did it come on
          suddenly, and was there any specific trigger you can think of?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>ACUTE (&lt; 2 weeks): <span class="infectious">Infectious (viral,
              bacterial), <b class="pharmacology">Medication-induced
                (antibiotics, metformin)</b>, <b class="General">Dietary
                indiscretion</b></span></li>
          <li>CHRONIC (&gt; 4 weeks): </li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="rheumatic">IBD (Crohn's, Ulcerative Colitis)</span>,</li>
            <li>&nbsp;<span class="git">IBS-D</span>,&nbsp;<span class="git"></span></li>
            <li><span class="git">Microscopic Colitis</span>, </li>
            <li><span class="git">Malabsorption (Celiac)</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li>Triggered by recent travel, new food, sick contacts, or starting a
            new medication?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration
          &amp; Frequency</span> <span class="verbal">"How long has this
          episode been going on for? And how many times a day are you having to
          go to the toilet?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"Does
          any particular food make it worse? Does eating in general, or does it
          improve after opening your bowels?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Worse with certain foods:&nbsp;<span class="git"></span></li>
          <li><span class="git">Lactose/Fructose intolerance, <br>
            </span></li>
          <li><span class="git">Fatty foods (malabsorption), <br>
            </span></li>
          <li><span class="git">Gluten (Celiac)</span></li>
          <li>Worse with stress: <span class="git">Irritable Bowel (IBS)</span></li>
          <li><span class="git">Antibiotics - difficale<br>
            </span></li>
        </ul>
        <p><br>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><span class="description">Relieving Factors</span></li>
          <li>after defecation: <span class="git">Classic for IBS</span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- C: Character -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character of Stool</span> <span class="verbal">"Can you describe the
          stool? Is it watery, bloody, greasy, or does it contain mucus?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>WATERY: <span class="infectious">Viral gastroenteritis (e.g.,
              Norovirus), <b class="infectious">Toxin-producing bacteria (e.g.,
                Cholera, E. coli)</b>, <b class="git">Microscopic colitis</b></span></li>
          <li>BLOODY (Hematochezia): <span class="rheumatic">IBD</span>, <span
              class="infectious">Infectious colitis (Shigella, Campylobacter,
              EHEC)</span>, <span class="git">Ischemic colitis</span>, <span class="oncology">Malignancy</span></li>
          <li>STEATORRHEA (Greasy, foul-smelling, floats): <span class="git endocrine">Malabsorption
              (e.g., Celiac disease, pancreatic insufficiency)</span></li>
          <li>MUCUS PRESENT: <span class="git">IBS</span>, <span class="rheumatic">IBD</span></li>
          <li>Volume: Large volume (small bowel) vs. Small volume (large bowel)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation (of Pain)</span> <span class="verbal">"If you have pain,
          does it travel or spread anywhere?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"Along with the
          diarrhea, have you experienced anything else like fever, vomiting, or
          weight loss?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>SYSTEMIC: <span class="infectious">Fever, chills, malaise
              (Infection)</span>, <span class="oncology">Unexplained weight
              loss (Malignancy, IBD, Malabsorption)</span></li>
          <li>GASTROINTESTINAL: <span class="infectious">Nausea, vomiting
              (Gastroenteritis)</span>, <span class="git">Tenesmus (feeling of
              incomplete evacuation) (Proctitis/IBD)</span>, <span class="git">Urgency,
              Incontinence</span></li>
          <li class="rheumatic">EXTRA-INTESTINAL (IBD clues): <span class="rheumatic">Joint
              pain, eye redness (uveitis), skin rashes (erythema nodosum)</span></li>
          <li class="nephro">SIGNS OF DEHYDRATION: <span class="nephro">Dizziness,
              reduced urine output, dry mouth, increased thirst</span></li>
          <li><span>Thryoid<br>
            </span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Since it started, has the
          diarrhea been getting better, worse, or staying about the same?"</span>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Is the diarrhea constant, or does it come and go?
          Do you have it at night?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>NOCTURNAL DIARRHEA (wakes from sleep): <b class="rheumatic oncology git">Red
              flag for organic disease (e.g., IBD, Microscopic Colitis), NOT
              typical for IBS</b></li>
          <li>ALTERNATING with constipation: <span class="git">Suggests IBS</span></li>
          <li>POST-PRANDIAL (after eating): <span class="git">Gastrocolic
              reflex, malabsorption, dumping syndrome</span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How has this been impacting your
          daily life, work, or ability to go out?"</span> </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific
          questions to make sure we're not missing anything serious."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="oncology git">Unexplained weight loss</li>
          <li class="hematology git">Rectal bleeding or iron-deficiency anemia</li>
          <li class="oncology git">New onset of symptoms in a person &gt; 50
            years old</li>
          <li class="oncology git">Strong family history of bowel cancer or IBD</li>
          <li class="rheumatic git">Nocturnal symptoms waking the patient from
            sleep</li>
          <li class="emergency infectious">Severe dehydration (dizziness,
            confusion, low urine output)</li>
          <li class="emergency infectious">High fever with severe abdominal pain</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Bother Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10,
          how much is this diarrhea bothering you or affecting your life?"</span>
      </li>
    </div>
